'''f. Write a Python program that does the following: 
i. Uses a loop for a user to continually input 5 values to populate an 
array. 
ii. Calculates  and  displays  the  average  of  the  values  input  into  the 
array. '''
import array as arr
import numpy as np
# Initializing integer array
numbers = arr.array('i',[])
# (i)Loop
while len(numbers) < 5:
    value = int(input("Please input a value: "))
    numbers.append(value)

# (ii)Output
print(np.mean(numbers))
